clouds-granular-pynq
====================

This product includes software developed independently, plus third-party
components noted below.

1. I2S serializer / deserializer (rtl/iis_deser.v, rtl/iis_ser.v)
   Converted to Verilog-2001 from the VHDL in the ADAU1761 IP of
   wady101/PYNQ_Z2-Audio  (https://github.com/wady101/PYNQ_Z2-Audio), MIT License.
   That code in turn derives from Digilent I2S reference designs. The conversion
   was validated bit-for-bit against the original VHDL (GHDL co-simulation)
   during development; the repository ships a self-contained Verilog loopback
   test (sim/tb_iis_loopback.sv) in its place.

2. Granular processing concept
   The granular engine is an independent RTL implementation inspired by the
   granular mode of Mutable Instruments "Clouds" (firmware MIT, by Emilie Gillet,
   https://github.com/pichenettes/eurorack). No original Clouds source code is
   used or included here. This project is not affiliated with or endorsed by
   Mutable Instruments.

Target hardware: TUL PYNQ-Z2 (Xilinx Zynq-7000, XC7Z020) with the on-board
Analog Devices ADAU1761 audio codec.
